author: CNN
description: Tony®, Golden Globe®, and four-time Emmy® Award-winning actor, Tony Shalhoub, journeys across the globe to share meals, stories, and traditions that reveal how bread connects us all. In Tony Shalhoub: Breaking Bread, he explores the universal power of food to bring people together. Watch the premiere Sunday October 5 on CNN.
title: Tony Shalhoub Tries The World’s Best Breads From Tokyo to Packers Stadium | Breaking Bread | CNN

author: CNN
description:
Of the more than 2,200 National Guard soldiers President Donald Trump deployed to Washington, DC last month, in addition to a wave of federal law enforcement, roughly 1,300 are from out of state. Guardsmen on the DC mission and their relatives who spoke to CNN said they left behind civilian jobs and children to serve – a sacrifice they understood when they enlisted.
And while domestic missions typically have National Guard troops responding to crises like hurricanes or wildfires, in DC, much of their work has involved more mundane tasks – patrolling popular tourist destinations and assisting with “beautification projects” including picking up trash, raking leaves and laying mulch.
CNN's Chief National Affairs Correspondent Jeff Zeleny joins CNN's Boris Sanchez for discussion.   #CNN #News
title: National Guard troops deployed to DC grow weary with no end in sight

author: CNN
description: Nearly three weeks after the US and Russian presidents failed to reach a peace deal to end Moscow's war in Ukraine, Europe is rushing to fill the diplomatic gap.  In Paris today, Kyiv's Western allies, known as the coalition of the willing, held talks with Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky. French President Emmanuel Macron says 26 nations have pledged to provide postwar security guarantees to Ukraine if a ceasefire is reached.  #CNN #News
title: Macron: Twenty-six nations vow to post-war security guarantees

author: CNN
description: As North Korean leader Kim Jong Un and Chinese leader Xi Jinping meet, CNN's Marc Stewart analyzes the relationship between the two countries. #CNN #news
title: Kim meets Xi a day after show of unity

author: CNN
description:
Health and Human Services Secretary Robert F. Kennedy Jr. testified in a heated hearing before a Senate committee today. Kennedy sparred with senators on vaccine policy, recent CDC shake-ups and public health. 

CNN chief medical correspondent Dr. Sanjay Gupta gives his take on Secretary Kennedy’s appearance before the Senate Finance Committee.  #CNN #News
title: Dr. Sanjay Gupta reacts to RFK Jr.’s fiery Senate testimony

author: CNN
description: More than a dozen people were killed in an accident on Lisbon’s famous Gloria funicular line, which has carried locals and tourists for more than a century, from Lisbon’s lively Restauradores Square up to Bairro Alto, one of the city’s oldest and most traditional neighborhoods. CNN takes a look at how the funicular actually works. #cnn #news
title: How Lisbon’s famous funicular works

author: CNN
description: "The Last of Us" and "Game of Thrones" star Bella Ramsey came face-to-face with a wax figure of herself now on display at Madame Tussauds London. #cnn #TheLastofUs #BellaRamsey #MadameTussauds #celebrities
title: Bella Ramsey meets wax version of herself

author: CNN
description:
Washington, DC, officials are suing the Trump administration, accusing the president of violating the Constitution and federal law by sending thousands of National Guard troops into the city without consent from local leaders. 

The lawsuit, filed Thursday by DC Attorney General Brian Schwalb, claims the troops – many from out of state – have been deputized by the US Marshals office and are patrolling neighborhoods, conducting searches and making arrests, despite federal laws that generally bar the military from acting as local police. #CNN #News
title: DC sues Trump administration over National Guard deployment

author: CNN
description: During a Senate hearing, Senator Elizabeth Warren (D)-MA asked HHS Secretary Robert Kennedy Jr. if the Covid-19 vaccine will be available. Recently, the FDA narrowed who is eligible for the vaccines, saying only adults over the age of 65 and younger people with certain medical conditions should get them.
title: Senator Warren presses RFK Jr. on covid vaccine availability

author: CNN
description:
Republican Sen. Bill Cassidy of Louisiana clashed with US Health and Human Services Secretary Robert F. Kennedy Jr. on the first Trump administration’s effort to develop new vaccines and treatments during the Covid-19 pandemic, picking at a divide between the health secretary and President Donald Trump.

Cassidy’s vote was decisive for Kennedy’s confirmation in February.  #CNN #News
title: Sen. Cassidy, a former physician, spars with Kennedy over mRNA vaccines

author: CNN
description: During a Senate hearing, HHS Secretary RFK Jr. said he did not know how many people died from Covid-19 in the United States. Data from Johns Hopkins University shows that more than one million Americans died from Covid-19.
title: Warner to RFK Jr.: How can you be that ignorant?

description: Victims of the convicted sex offender Jeffrey Epstein said they would compile their own list of abusers if all of the information related to the case is not publicly released. Republican lawmakers who are pushing for more transparency said they are willing to read the names on the House floor if a list is available. #cnn #news #politics

author: CNN
description: During a Senate hearing, HHS Secretary Robert Kennedy Jr. accused the former CDC Director Susan Monarez of lying. In a WSJ op-ed, Monarez says she was told to pre-approve childhood vaccine recommendations by new appointees to a vaccine advisory committee. The White House recently removed Monarez from her position.
title: RFK Jr. accuses the ex-CDC director of lying to Wall Street Journal

author: CNN
description:
Italian fashion designer Giorgio Armani has died at the age of 91, the Armani Group announced on Thursday.

The designer is credited over his decades of practice with curating a quintessentially Italian aesthetic in his clothes, as well as taking Hollywood’s red carpets to new heights.   #CNN #News
title: Italian fashion designer Giorgio Armani dies aged 91

author: CNN
description:
Italian fashion designer Giorgio Armani has died at the age of 91, the Armani Group announced. “Il Signor Armani, as he was always respectfully and admiringly called by employees and collaborators, passed away peacefully, surrounded by his loved ones,” the Armani Group said in a statement, describing the founder as “a tireless driving force.”

#cnn #news #armani #fashion
title: Giorgio Armani dead at age 91

author: CNN
description: There is “deliberate” effort by the Trump administration to weaken the US public health system and vaccine protections, Dr. Susan Monarez, who was removed from her position as director of the US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, wrote in a Wall Street Journal opinion piece. #CNN #News
title: Ousted CDC director: There is a ‘deliberate effort to weaken’ the US public health system

author: CNN
description:
A New Jersey man showed off his dance moves during a town hall meeting in Cranford, New Jersey and then discussed an increase in taxes due to a local referendum. Will Thilly has a record of unconventional town hall appearances that he frequently posts on Instagram.

#cnn #news #newjersey #breakdance
title: Man breakdances, backspins, talks about taxes at town hall then moonwalks away

author: CNN
description:
President Donald Trump urged the Supreme Court to step into the fray over his emergency tariffs, putting the centerpiece of his economic agenda in the hands of the justices who have mostly backed his sweeping view of executive power, according to a copy of the appeal obtained by CNN. 

Trump is pressing the justices to overturn a lower court ruling that found his administration acted unlawfully by imposing many of his sweeping import taxes, and he has framed the case in existential terms. #CNN #News
title: Trump asks Supreme Court to save his emergency tariffs

author: CNN
description: CNN's Dr. Sanjay Gupta explores how meditation, a practice involving calmness and focus, can reduce pain intensity and unpleasantness. Watch “Dr. Sanjay Gupta Reports: It Doesn’t Have to Hurt.” at 9 p.m. ET on September 7 on CNN. #cnn #health #meditation #pain
title: How meditation can reduce pain sensation

author: CNN
description:
The deadly US military strike on an alleged drug boat in the Caribbean Tuesday marked a significant and escalatory shift in the Trump administration’s fight against drug trafficking, as Secretary of State Marco Rubio signaled there would be more destruction moving forward. 

Rubio on Wednesday argued that the traditional policy of intercepting drug-carrying vessels had not worked. Instead, the US is “going to wage war on narco-terrorist organizations.” #CNN #News
title: US-Venezuela tensions rising after airstrike

author: CNN
description: Surveillance footage from a gun store shows Minnesota church shooter Robin Westman appearing “normal” and interacting positively with staff while shopping for guns days before a Catholic school tragedy, the owner said. #cnn #minnesotashooting
title: Video shows Minnesota church shooter at gun shop days before tragedy

author: CNN
description: The European Union has banned a common chemical used in many gel nail polishes. It says more research is needed to examine a possible link between the chemical and damage to the reproductive system. The product is not currently banned in the UK and the US.
title: Why has the EU banned some gel nail polish?

author: CNN
description:
A federal judge on Wednesday gave Harvard University a landmark victory in its fight against the Trump administration, siding with the Ivy League school in its effort to restore more than $2 billion in federal funding for research frozen by the White House. 

The decision from US District Judge Allison Burroughs rejects the administration’s argument that it was targeting the university due to antisemitism on the school’s campus.  #CNN #News
title: Harvard wins landmark victory against Trump administration

author: CNN
description: Sources tell CNN the Trump administration have floated the idea of offering New York Mayor Eric Adams a job ahead of the election in November. It's an apparent effort to clear the field and boost Andrew Cuomo, and prevent Democratic-Socialist Zohran Mamdani from winning. #CNN #News
title: Ben Ferguson: Trump genuinely concerned about socialist running NYC

author: CNN
description:
Audie calls up comedian and longtime television producer Larry Wilmore to find out what’s driving Hollywood’s pronounced shift away from the hard lean into wokeness we saw just a few years ago. Is this a lasting change, or just another spin of the wheel in studios’ chase for the next big thing?

Listen to the full episode of CNN's The Assignment podcast: http://swap.fm/l/tawacyt090425

#cnn #news #tv #entertainment
title: Larry Wilmore decodes TV in 2025 | The Assignment

description:
Trump has pledged to make the US the “crypto capital of the planet,” and his own wealth, pursued by his sons and business partners, is increasingly dependent on cryptocurrency.
Podcast host Kara Swisher joins CNN's Kaitlan Collins on "The Source" for a discussion.
#CNN #News
title: Trump primed to cash in on crypto gold rush he's helped create

author: CNN
description: A bipartisan group of lawmakers stood outside the US Capitol on Wednesday alongside nearly a dozen women who said they’d been abused by the late convicted sex offender Jeffrey Epstein with a poignant message: This is not a hoax. That included a direct plea from one of the survivors, Anouska de Georgiou, to the president: “President Trump, you have so much influence and power in this situation. Please use that influence and power to help us.” And an invite extended to him from another abuse survivor, Haley Robson: “I cordially invite you to the Capitol to meet me in person so you can understand this is not a hoax. We are real human beings. This is real trauma.” #CNN #News
title: Rep Massie: 'Rich and powerful people' behind Trump's shift of Epstein

author: CNN
description: Police in Florida have released body camera video showing a man in a Chuck E. Cheese mascot uniform arrested at one of the chain’s Florida venues. The employee was charged with credit card theft and fraud charges.
title: Man arrested wearing Chuck E. Cheese costume

At least 15 people were killed and several were injured by a derailment on a funicular railway in Lisbon, Portugal, according to a police source who spoke with CNN Portugal.

#CNN #News
